			LESS js available if needed e.g not working localhost
			
			The idea behind LESS is to speed up and simplify only the development step. 
			This means what goes live on your final website should be plain old CSS, not LESS.

			After youâ€™re finished working on your site, you need only compile the LESS into CSS and copy and paste it into styles.css
			
			While using LESS js you need to remove the normal CSS stylesheet and include less.min.js. As well as manually
			adding your LESS styles within head.phtml using the rel="stylesheet/less" like this : 
			
			<link rel="stylesheet/less" type="text/css" href="<?php echo $this->getSkinUrl('less/styles.less'); ?>" />
			
			(unfortunately magento doesn't have the ability to change the rel tag in xml so it has to be hard coded... nasty!)
			--> 
	        
